IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: OUR MISSION IS TO END HUNGER.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE GREATER CHICAGO FOOD DEPOSITORY IS THE NONPROFIT FOOD BANK SERVING COOK COUNTY. OUR MISSION - IS TO END HUNGER. WE BELIEVE FOOD IS A BASIC HUMAN RIGHT. TO ACHIEVE OUR MISSION, WE WORK IN PARTNERSHIP WITH A NETWORK OF COMMUNITY-BASED ORGANIZATIONS AND INDIVIDUALS.
IRS990.Desc: THE GREATER CHICAGO FOOD DEPOSITORY PROVIDES EMERGENCY FOOD ASSISTANCE IN COOK COUNTY, ILLINOIS BY DISTRIBUTING FOOD THROUGH A NETWORK OF MORE THAN 800 FOOD PANTRIES, SOUP KITCHENS, SHELTERS AND PROGRAMS. THE FOOD DISTRIBUTED IS DONATED, PURCHASED OR RECEIVED FROM FEDERAL PROGRAMS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: THE GREATER CHICAGO FOOD DEPOSITORY PROVIDES PROGRAMS TO ALLEVIATE HUNGER AMONG PRIORITY POPULATIONS INCLUDING CHILDREN, STUDENTS, OLDER ADULTS AND VETERANS. THE ORGANIZATION ALSO OFFERS WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT FOR UNEMPLOYED AND UNDEREMPLOYED INDIVIDUALS. OTHER PROGRAMS INCLUDE AFTER-SCHOOL AND SUMMER MEALS FOR CHILDREN, FOOD DISTRIBUTIONS FOR OLDER ADULTS, FOOD DISTRIBUTIONS AT SCHOOLS, AND FEDERAL BENEFITS OUTREACH.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: MOBILE RESPONSES REACH POPULATIONS THAT OFTEN DON'T HAVE ACCESS TO TRADITIONAL EMERGENCY ASSISTANCE PROGRAMS. THE FOOD DEPOSITORY'S PRODUCE MOBILE DISTRIBUTES FRESH FRUIT AND VEGETABLES IN HIGH-NEED COMMUNITIES, WHILE THE MOBILE PANTRY PROVIDES PRODUCE, PROTEIN AND SHELF-STABLE GROCERIES TO HUNGRY INDIVIDUALS ON EVENINGS AND WEEKENDS. THE FRESH TRUCK OFFERS PRODUCE TO FOOD INSECURE PATIENTS OF HEALTH CLINICS THROUGHOUT COOK COUNTY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S ADVOCACY AGENDA SUPPORTS HUNGER RELIEF EFFORTS ANNUALLY IN SPRINGFIELD AND WASHINGTON D.C. STAFF MEET WITH AND SEND LETTERS AND OTHER INFORMATION TO ELECTED OFFICIALS, THEIR STAFFS, AND/OR GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS REGARDING PENDING LEGISLATION AND ADMINISTRATIVE ISSUES RELATED TO HUNGER RELIEF PROGRAMS OR OTHER ANTI-POVERTY ISSUES. WE ALSO PERIODICALLY PUBLISH REPORTS AND SUMMARIES ON THESE KEY ISSUES THAT ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO ELECTED AND GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS AND THE GENERAL PUBLIC. THE ORGANIZATION ALSO WORKS TO INFORM AND MOBILIZE GRASSROOTS VOLUNTEERS ON IMPORTANT PUBLIC POLICY ISSUES.

THE OBJECTIVES OF THE FOUNDERS' FUND AND THE BOARD-DESIGNATED FREEDOM FROM HUNGER FUND ENDOWMENTS ARE (1) TO PROVIDE A POOL OF CAPITAL SUFFICIENT TO FUND THE OPERATING RESERVE; (2) TO PROVIDE A SOURCE OF FUNDS FOR TARGETED CAPITAL PROJECTS, PROGRAMMATIC GROWTH, AND OTHER USES AS DEEMED APPROPRIATE BY THE FOOD DEPOSITORY'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS (THE "BOARD"), CONSISTENT WITH THE FOOD DEPOSITORY'S STRATEGIC PLAN; AND (3) TO PROVIDE AN IDENTIFIED PORTION OF THE FUND TO THE ANNUAL OPERATING BUDGET OF THE FOOD DEPOSITORY TO PAY OPERATING EXPENSES. THE FIRST TWO OBJECTIVES ARE FOR LONG-TERM INVESTMENT GOALS, WHILE THE THIRD OBJECTIVE MEETS SHORT-TERM INVESTMENT AND LIQUIDITY NEEDS.

THE FOOD DEPOSITORY IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT CORPORATION AND IS EXEMPT FROM TAX UNDER THE PROVISIONS OF INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 501(C)(3). ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA REQUIRE MANAGEMENT TO EVALUATE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN BY THE FOOD DEPOSITORY AND RECOGNIZE A TAX LIABILITY IF THE FOOD DEPOSITORY HAS TAKEN AN UNCERTAIN POSITION THAT MORE LIKELY THAN NOT WOULD NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY THE IRS OR OTHER APPLICABLE TAXING AUTHORITIES. MANAGEMENT HAS ANALYZED THE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN BY THE FOOD DEPOSITORY AND HAS CONCLUDED THAT, AS OF JUNE 30, 2023 AND 2022, THERE ARE NO UNCERTAIN POSITIONS TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN THAT WOULD REQUIRE RECOGNITION OF A LIABILITY OR DISCLOSURE IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE FOOD DEPOSITORY IS SUBJECT TO ROUTINE AUDITS BY TAXING JURISDICTIONS; HOWEVER, THERE ARE CURRENTLY NO AUDITS FOR ANY TAX PERIODS IN PROGRESS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ORGANIZATION HAS A FORMAL APPLICATION AND REVIEW PROCESS FOR ACCEPTING NEW PARTNER AGENCIES. ONCE ACCEPTED, AGENCIES MUST SUBMIT A FOLLOW-UP REPORT INDICATING HOW THE MONEY OR PROPERTY WAS USED AND PROVIDE RECEIPTS AND OTHER DOCUMENTATION. ANNUALLY, GCFD PERFORMS A COMPLIANCE REVIEW FOR EACH PARTNER AGENCY.

AS INDICATED IN SCHEDULE J, PART II, CERTAIN INDIVIDUALS RECEIVED DISCRETIONARY BONUSES BASED ON PERFORMANCE. THE CEO'S BONUS IS APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, OTHER STAFF BONUSES ARE APPROVED BY THE CEO. THE BONUSES ARE TYPICALLY A RESULT OF MEETING OR EXCEEDING ORGANIZATIONAL GOALS.
THE ORGANIZATION USES THE SERVICES OF AN INDEPENDENT STOCK BROKER TO SELL DONATED STOCK IMMEDIATELY UPON RECEIPT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVERNING BODY REVIEW OF FORM 990 - THE BOARD RETAINS THE SERVICES OF AN INDEPENDENT CPA FIRM TO PREPARE THE ORGANIZATION'S FORM 990. MANAGEMENT REVIEWS THE COMPLETED FORM 990 AND PROVIDES A FULL COPY TO ALL VOTING MEMBERS OF THE GOVERNING BODY PRIOR TO FILING. THE BOARD IS PROVIDED A REASONABLE AMOUNT OF TIME TO REVIEW THE RETURN AND ASK ANY QUESTIONS DIRECTLY TO GREATER CHICAGO FOOD DEPOSITORY'S MANAGEMENT OR THE CONTACT AT THE INDEPENDENT CPA FIRM PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CONFLICTS OF INTEREST POLICY MONITORING - OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, AND KEY EMPLOYEES ARE ANNUALLY REQUIRED TO COMPLETE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST DISCLOSURE STATEMENT AS A PRECURSOR TO THEIR SERVICE TO THE ORGANIZATION. POTENTIAL CONFLICTS ARE LOGGED WITH AND MONITORED BY THE BOARD LEGAL COUNSEL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GREATER CHICAGO FOOD DEPOSITORY HIRED A COMPENSATION CONSULTING FIRM, COMMONWEALTH HR CONSULTING (CHRC), IN 2022 TO CONDUCT MARKET PRICING FOR ALL ITS POSITIONS EXCEPT THE VICE PRESIDENT AND CHIEF POSITIONS. IN 2023, AJ GALLAGHER PERFORMED A MARKET COMPARISON FOR THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER POSITION TO ENSURE CEO COMPENSATION IS COMPETITIVE. THE GREATER CHICAGO FOOD DEPOSITORY USES THE FOLLOWING SOURCES OF DATA: - ECONOMIC RESEARCH INSTITUTE, INC. ("ERI") - COMPANALYST MARKET DATA (PROFESSIONAL VERSION OF SALARY.COM) - PAYSCALE THE GREATER CHICAGO FOOD DEPOSITORY ALSO USES DATA FROM THE LIVING WAGE CALCULATOR THAT INCLUDES RESEARCH DONE BY THE MASSACHUSETTS INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY (MIT) TO DETERMINE COMPENSATION RATES FOR EMPLOYEES IN 2023. THE GREATER CHICAGO FOOD DEPOSITORY USES THE FOLLOWING CRITERIA: - NONPROFIT OR ALL INDUSTRIES, DEPENDING ON THE POSITION. - HIGHER EDUCATION, HEALTH CARE, AND ARTS & CULTURE (DEVELOPMENT). - CHICAGO AREA OR REGIONAL OR NATIONAL, DEPENDING ON THE POSITION. - REVENUE - $100 MILLION/200 FULL-TIME EMPLOYEES. THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER (CEO), CHIEF OPERATION OFFICER AND VICE PRESIDENT OF PEOPLE & CULTURE REVIEW AND APPROVE STAFF COMPENSATION ANNUALLY. THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEWS AND APPROVES CEO COMPENSATION WITH FINAL APPROVAL BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PUBLIC DISCLOSURE OF DOCUMENTS - GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE THROUGH APPLICABLE GOVERNMENTAL AGENCIES; THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST OF THE ORGANIZATION.

IN 2018, THE FOOD DEPOSITORY LAUNCHED THE NOURISH CAPITAL CAMPAIGN. THE CAMPAIGN SEEKS TO RAISE APPROXIMATELY $75 MILLION TO SUPPORT CAPITAL IMPROVEMENTS TO THE EXISTING FOOD DEPOSITORY FACILITY AND EXPANSION OF THE FACILITY TO EXPAND PROGRAMMATIC CAPABILITIES.
